
[1]purely

   PU'RELY, adv. In a pure manner; with an entire separation of
   heterogeneous or foul matter. Is.1.

   1. Without any mixture of improper or vicious words or phrases.

   2. Innocently; without guilt.

   3. Merely; absolutely; without connection with any thing else;
   completely; totally. The meeting was purely accidental.
